<topic template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2022-03-03T20:06:50.745Z" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Indexer</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Indexer Keywords<keyword>Dwell-Period</keyword><keyword>Index-Angle</keyword><keyword>Index-Period</keyword><keyword>Number-of-Stops</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Indexer</text> is a pre-assembled, cam driven device, with input-shaft (or -hollow-shaft) and output-shaft (or dial). The output-shaft moves with a <text style="font-style:italic;">progressive</text> motion while the input-shaft rotates continuously. A Progressive motion is one that moves, then usually dwells, and repeats with a series of identical motions. After a number of identical progressive motions, the output-shaft returns to its original position. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Some definitions used with <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Indexers</text>:</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline; color:#808000;">NUMBER-OF-STOPS</text>: The number of times the input shaft must rotate to for the output shaft one complete cycle. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline; color:#804040;">INDEX-ANGLE</text>: the angle that the output shaft rotates each time one index motion is complete. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Note</text>: Index Angle (degrees) = 360 / Number-of-Stops.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline; color:#008000;">INDEX-PERIOD</text>: The rotation, in degrees, of the input shaft to complete the INDEX.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text style="font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline; color:#b97034;">DWELL-PERIOD</text>: The rotation of the input shaft to complete the DWELL. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Note: index-period + DWELL PERIOD</text> = 360. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:0px;">Sometimes there are two <text style="font-style:italic;">&apos;Stops&apos;</text> for each rotation of the input shaft.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
